                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2195Prover">Proverbs</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     <note>The text, which has been translated from the Greek <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1219Bible#t6greekLXX"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT1219Bible#t6greekLXX</span></ref>, seems to have also been corrected
                        according to it.</note>


                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.1">
                        <title type="complete" xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3927Messale">ምሳልያተ፡
                           ያዴዲ</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        <note>Chapter 1 (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ክፍል፡ ፩</foreign>) contains verses
                           6-19. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ክፍል</foreign> is also written at the
                           following places (chapter and verse indications according to the Hebrew
                           text): <p>1:20;</p>
                           <p>9:12;</p>
                           <p>14:31;</p>
                           <p>18:22;</p>
                           <p>21:22;</p>
                           <p>30:15.</p>
                        </note>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">ምሳልያተ፡ ሰሎሞን፡ ወልደ፡ ዳዊት፡ ዘነግሠ፡ ለእስራኤል፡ ለአእምሮ፡ ጥበብ፡
                           ወተግሣጽ፡ ወለአእምሮ፡ ቃለ፡ ጥበብ፡ ወለተወከፎ፡ ተመይጦ፡ ቃል፡ ወለአእምሮ፡ ጽድቅ፡ ዘበአማን። ወፍትሐ፡ ለአርትዖ
                              <supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> ከመ፡
                           የሃቦሙ፡ ጥበበ፡ ለየውሓን። ለሕፃናት፡ ወለወሬዛ፡ ተዓውቆ፡ አእምሮ። ዘንተ፡ እምከመ፡ ሰምዓ፡ ጠቢብ፡ ጥበበ፡
                           ይዌስክ፡ ወዘሰ፡ አጥርየ፡ ሐዳፈ፡ የአምር፡ ምሳሌ፡ ወስውረ፡ ነገረ፤ ነገረ፡ ጠቢባን፡ በቅጽበት።</incipit>
                        <note>The Ethiopic title, <foreign xml:lang="gez">mǝssālǝyāta
                              Yādedi</foreign>, refers to the name <foreign xml:lang="he">Yǝdidyah</foreign> given to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8925Solomon">Solomon</persName> in 2
                           Kings 12:25.</note>
                     </msItem>

                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i2.2">
                        <locus from="17v">Fols 17v and following</locus>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2396Tagsas">Tagśāṣa
                                                  Salomon</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        <note>There is a division only at the beginning of the praise of the strong
                           woman, chapter 30:10 (according to the Hebrew text, corresponds to <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1219Bible#t6greekLXX">Septuagint</ref>,
                           chapter 31:10)</note>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">ተግሣጽ፡ ዘሰሎሞን፡ እለ፡ እንበለ፡ ኑፋቄ፡ ዘጸሐፉ፡ አዕርክቲሁ፡ ለሕዝቅያስ፡
                           ንጉሠ፡ ይሁዳ<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied>
                           ክብረ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ የኀብእ፡ ነውረ፡ ወስብሐተ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ያከብር፡ ገብረ<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> ሰማይ፡ ልዑል፡ ወምድር፡
                           ዕሙቅ፡ ወልበ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ኢይትአመር<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> ዝብጦ፡ ለብሩር፡ ዘኢኮነ፡ ፍቱን፡ ወይነጽሕ፡ ለከ፡ ንጽሐ፡ ፍጹመ<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> ቅትል፡ ረሲዓን፡
                           እምቅድመ፡ ገጸ፡ ንጉሥ፡</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <locus from="21r">Fols 21r and following</locus>
                     <title type="complete" xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1320Eccles">መጽሐፈ፡ ቀሐልት፡</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     <note>There are no divisions. </note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez"> ቃለ፡ መክብብ፡ ወልደ፡ ዳዊት፡ ንጉሠ፡ እስራኤል፡ ዘኢየሩዳሌም<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> ከንቱ፡ ከንቱ፡ ይቤ፡
                        መክብብ፡ ኵሉ፡ ከንቱ<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> ምንት፡ ፍድፋዴሁ፡ ለሰብእ፡ በኵሉ፡ ፃማሁ፡ ዘይፃሙ፡ እምታሕተ፡ ፀሐይ<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> ትውልድ፡ የኀልፍ፡ ወትውልድ፡
                        ይመጽእ፡ ወምድርሰ፡ ለዓለም፡ ይነብር<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> ይሠርቅ፡ ፀሐይ፡ ወየዓርብ፡ ፀሐይ፡ 
                        
                        <choice>
                           <sic resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">ውውስተ</sic>
                           <corr resp="DR">ወውስተ</corr>
                        </choice>
                        
                        ፡ መካኑ፡ ይገብእ፡ ይሠርቅ፡ ውእቱ፡ ህየ፡ </incipit>
                     <note>See also <ref target="#chapter12"/>
                     </note>
                     <note>The text has been translated from the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1219Bible#t6greekLXX"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT1219Bible#t6greekLXX</span></ref>.</note>
                     <note>The title has been added later.</note>
                  </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4">
                     <locus from="27v">Fols 27v and following</locus>
                     <title type="complete" xml:lang="gez" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2516Wisdom">ጥበበ፡ ሰሎሞን፡ ወልደ፡ ዳዊት፡
                        ዘነግሠ፡ ላዕለ፡ እስራኤል።</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     <note>Chapter divisions begin after the introduction, which corresponds to
                        chapter 1 of the original Greek text. They are marked at the following
                        passages: <p>2:1; 2:12; 2:24;</p>
                        <p>5:1;</p>
                        <p>6:1;</p>
                        <p>8:2; 8:21b;</p>
                        <p>10:1;</p>
                        <p>11:1; 11:27;</p>
                        <p>12:3;</p>
                        <p>14:14;</p>
                        <p>15:1;</p>
                        <p>16:1; 16:27.</p>
                     </note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">አፍቅርዋ፡ ለጽድቅ፡ ኦመኳንንተ፡ ምድር፡ ወኀልዩ፡ ኀይለ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በአእምሮ፡
                        ሠናይ፡ ወበስፋሕ፡ ልብ፡ ኅሥዎ፡ እስመ፡ ውእቱ፡ ይትረከብ፡ በኀበ፡ እለ፡ ኢያሜክርዎ፡ ወያስተርኢ፡ በኀበ፡ እለ፡
                        ኢይክህድዎ። እስመ፡ ጠዋይ፡ ሕሊና፡ ያርኅቅ፡ እምእግዚአብሔር፡ ወኀይል፡ ፍትንት፡ ትዛለፎሙ፡ ለአብዳን<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> እስመ፡ ውስተ፡ ምይንት፡
                        ነፍስ፡ ኢትበውዕ፡ ጥበብ፡ ወኢተኀድር፡ ውስተ፡ ሥጋ፡ ዘቅኑይ፡ ለኀጢአት<supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">።</supplied> እስመ፡ መንፈስ፡ ተግሣጽ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ያጐይይ፡ ትምህርተ፡
                        ዘእሉይ፡</incipit>
                  </msItem>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i5">
                     <locus from="43r">Fols 43r and following</locus>
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2358Sirach">Book of
                                                  Sirach</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     <note>In 1:25, there is another title: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ትምህርተ፡ ጥበብ፡ ወቃለ፡
                           ተግሣጽ፡ ጸሐፍኩ፡ ውስተ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አነ፡ ኢያሱ፡ ሲራክ፡ ወልደ፡ ሲራክ፡ ወልደ፡ አልዓዛር፡
                           ዘኢየሩሳሌም።</foreign>
                     </note>
                     <note>Both titles have been added later.</note>
                     
                     <incipit xml:lang="gez">ጥበብ፡ ዘተከሥተት፡ በኢየሩሳሌም፡ ቀዳሚሃ። ኵላ ጥበብ፡ እምኀበ፡
                        እግዚአብሔር፡</incipit>
                     <note>The text is the same one as in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet6#ms_i7"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: BNFet6#ms_i7</span></ref>,
                        except for many variants.</note>
                     <note>The text is divided into sections.</note>
                  </msItem>


                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i6">
                     <locus from="91v">Fols 91v and following</locus>
                     <title type="incomplete">Spiritual Genealogy of the Ethiopian monks in
                        Jerusalem</title>
                     
                     <note>The end has been erased.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                     <incipit xml:lang="am">መጽሐፈ፡ ልደቱ፡ ዘወጽአ፡ እምኢየሩሳሌም። ባ፡ ቢወልድ፡ አርባሕን። አርባሕን፡ ቢወልድ፡
                        አጽባሕን። አጽባሕ፡ ቢወልድ፡ ቍር። <supplied reason="undefined" resp="PRS10747Zotenbe">ቍር፡</supplied>ቢወልድ፡ አብቍርን። አብቍር፡ ቢወልድ፡ ኀበለምን። </incipit>
                  </msItem>

               </msContents>

